text: Harlem is an unincorporated community in Winnebago County, in the U.S. state of Illinois. ==History== A post office called Harlem was established in 1839, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1928. The community was named after Harlem, New York. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Winnebago County, Illinois Category:Unincorporated communities in Illinois
title: Harlem, Illinois
